17:34.000 --> 17:35.250
<i>Masato Ono.</i>

17:36.375 --> 17:39.833
<i>Prime Minister, you said</i>
<i>it doesn't concern you and brushed it off,</i>

17:40.416 --> 17:43.125
<i>but your name and the First Lady's name</i>

17:43.208 --> 17:44.958
<i>have come up in relation</i>

17:45.041 --> 17:48.041
<i>to the establishment</i>
<i>of this school several times.</i>

17:50.541 --> 17:53.708
<i>I highly doubt the public will be</i>
<i>satisfied with that explanation.</i>

17:53.791 --> 17:56.000
ASSISTANT TO THE FIRST LADY

17:56.083 --> 17:57.041
<i>Prime Minister!</i>

17:59.083 --> 18:03.416
<i>Can you categorically deny</i>
<i>that you had influence in this matter?</i>

18:03.500 --> 18:05.083
THE FIVE BUREAUCRATS
WHO SUPPORT THE FIRST LADY

18:05.166 --> 18:06.166
<i>Mr. Prime Minister.</i>

18:08.208 --> 18:10.333
PHOTO OF FIRST LADY'S ASSISTANTS
SHINICHI MURAKAMI

18:10.416 --> 18:12.625
<i>I can definitively state</i>

18:12.708 --> 18:16.333
<i>that there is absolutely no truth</i>
<i>to the claims that I was involved in</i>

18:16.416 --> 18:19.083
<i>the sale of the land</i>
<i>or the approval of the sale.</i>

18:21.333 --> 18:25.083
<i>If I or my wife were involved</i>
<i>in this in any way,</i>

18:25.833 --> 18:28.125
<i>then of course</i>

18:28.208 --> 18:35.166
<i>I will step down as prime minister</i>
<i>and resign from the National Diet.</i>

18:35.250 --> 18:36.708
<i>Well said, Prime Minister!</i>

18:38.416 --> 18:39.708
KITAMURA

18:40.458 --> 18:41.625
Hello?

18:41.708 --> 18:44.041
Hi. Did you hear what the PM said?

18:44.125 --> 18:46.375
-Yes.
<i>-What do you think?</i>

18:49.125 --> 18:53.875
That last part, he clearly ignored
the statement that was prepared for him.

18:55.375 --> 18:57.916
I think he was speaking
using his own words.

18:59.125 --> 19:00.916
If he turns out to be lying,

19:01.000 --> 19:03.166
this could cause
his administration's downfall.

19:06.625 --> 19:07.500
That's right.

19:08.750 --> 19:10.750
I need to finish some research
here in Tokyo.

19:10.833 --> 19:12.791
But after that, I'll travel to Nagoya

19:12.875 --> 19:15.875
and get info from those close
to the Chubu Local Finance Bureau.

19:16.458 --> 19:17.458
<i>Got it.</i>

19:18.166 --> 19:20.125
Goodbye.

19:25.958 --> 19:27.458
I wasn't expecting that.

19:30.541 --> 19:33.375
I wish he'd stick to the script.

19:35.166 --> 19:40.333
At any rate,
put a muzzle on everyone involved.

19:40.416 --> 19:42.041
We can't have them talk about this.

19:42.125 --> 19:44.250
Certainly.
I'll take care of it right away.

19:46.791 --> 19:49.083
-Murakami.
-Yes?

19:53.083 --> 19:57.333
I doubt we can keep what
the Ministry of Finance knows under wraps.

19:59.125 --> 20:00.041
Right.

20:02.541 --> 20:05.583
I want you to tell Finance Bureau
Director-General Mouri about this.

20:05.666 --> 20:06.708
Yes, sir.

20:09.416 --> 20:13.375
The Prime Minister's Office
has had nothing to do with this affair.

20:18.875 --> 20:21.708
But I negotiated the deal
with the Ministry of Finance.

20:21.791 --> 20:22.625
I know that!

20:25.583 --> 20:27.500
I know, butâ€¦

