20:37.208 --> 20:38.291
I'm counting on you.

20:50.708 --> 20:52.125
I'm home.

20:52.958 --> 20:53.958
Welcome home.

20:55.583 --> 20:59.083
I'm home. What a nice smell!

20:59.166 --> 21:01.416
It's not quite ready.
Why don't you take a bath first?

21:02.000 --> 21:04.375
I'm starving. I'd rather eat first.

21:04.458 --> 21:06.666
Fine. Hold on a minute.

21:09.333 --> 21:11.291
Is Mr. Kurosaki doing well?

21:11.375 --> 21:13.750
Yes. The same as ever.

21:14.750 --> 21:17.208
He's a veteran I can always rely on.

21:17.291 --> 21:19.041
I'm glad to hear it.

21:19.625 --> 21:22.166
But don't push yourself
too hard and overdo it.

21:23.125 --> 21:25.166
You bet I'll push myself.

21:25.250 --> 21:27.958
We national civil servants
work for the people of this country.

21:28.041 --> 21:30.333
We need to work the hardest
during hard days.

21:31.375 --> 21:35.333
You have always been
proud of doing your utmost for the people.

21:35.416 --> 21:36.541
That's right.

21:39.000 --> 21:40.333
It's Mr. Kurosaki.

21:42.291 --> 21:43.208
Hello?

21:44.583 --> 21:47.833
Yes, it's okay. What is it?

21:49.708 --> 21:50.666
Okay.

21:52.000 --> 21:52.833
Okay.

21:54.291 --> 21:55.291
Now?

21:56.750 --> 21:58.500
No, it's all right.

21:59.416 --> 22:03.375
All right. Okay, bye.

22:05.916 --> 22:09.833
I'm sorry, Mayumi.
He wants me back there immediately.

22:09.916 --> 22:11.500
Really? Now?

22:11.583 --> 22:16.208
Yes. But since it's Mr. Kurosaki asking,
I should go.

22:17.083 --> 22:19.958
Okay. Tell Mr. Kurosaki I said hello.

22:20.041 --> 22:20.958
Sure.

22:25.125 --> 22:27.583
-Take care.
-I'll be home soon.

22:46.333 --> 22:48.583
Mr. Kurosaki. Good evening.

22:49.916 --> 22:52.125
Sorry to call you here so suddenly.

22:52.208 --> 22:54.375
It's okay. What is it?

22:56.291 --> 22:59.625
